---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Form from "../components/Form.astro";
import Banner from "../components/Banner.astro";
import Border from "../components/Border.astro";
import Counter from "../components/Counter.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Avaya"
  description="Avaya"
>
  <header class="py-5">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row align-items-center">
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
          <div class="pe-lg-5">
            <h1 class="hero__title text-black mb-3 pe-lg-5">
              "It has made <br>
us more focused <br>
on the actual communication rather than <br>
how we communicate.”
            </h1>
            <p class="hero__description text-black fs-5">
              - Avaya customer on TrustRadius
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
          <Border style="border-4">
            <img class="w-100 mx-auto d-block" src="assets/hero.jpg" alt="man and woman talking" fetchpriority="high">
          </Border>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row mt-5">
        <div class="col">
          <p>
            Customer expectations are high, and their patience can sometimes be short. Organizations need to ensure they are as well-equipped as possible – from offering options for customers to contact them to ensuring the right resources are available at all times. However, it needs to happen effortlessly.  
          </p> 
          <p>
            With Avaya Experience Platform, organizations are empowered to synchronize employees, resources, insights, processes, and knowledge across their entire organization to maximize performance and build brand advocacy, all served from a hassle-free, always-on, secure cloud. We support you on your journey to the cloud – based on your personalized needs – so that you can accelerate new experiences to consumers and employees.
          </p>
          <p>
            But don’t just take our word for it – here’s what our customers think.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>


  <section class="my-5">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
          <h2 class="text-center fw-bold mb-4 fs-1">
            What customers are saying:
          </h2>
          <p class="text-center">
            Check out Avaya Experience Platform ratings from independent review site TrustRadius.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
          <div class="trustradius-tqw" style="height: 450px; background-color: #FFFFFF;" data-trustradius-id="6050e433dc45420036d51ebc"></div><script src="https://www.trustradius.com/trustquotes/trustquotes.js" type="text/javascript" async></script>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>



  <main class="bg-blue-feather">
    <div class="container py-5">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
          <div class="my-5">
            <h2 class="text-white text-center fs-1 fw-bold mb-5">
              Is your organization living up to your <br>
              customers’ expectations?
            </h2>
            <p class="text-white text-center">
              Great customer experience is a must for any organization looking to stay competitive in today’s market. Customers are expecting a seamless and connected experience each and every time. With an ever-changing contact center, your customer experience strategies need to adapt. Here’s why:
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row pb-5" id="counter-section">
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
          <Counter number="80" text="Of consumers would rather do business with your competitor after just one bad experience" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
          <Counter number="76" text="Of consumers admit they would stop doing business with your organization after just one bad experience" /> 
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
          <Counter number="57" text="Of one-star reviews are directly related to poor customer experience" />
        </div>
      </div>
   
      <hr class="text-white p-0 m-0">
      <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-8">
          <div class="d-flex flex-column flex-lg-row gap-5 py-3 mt-5 justify-content-around mb-4 align-items-center">
            <h2 class="text-white text-center fw-bold fs-1">
              Download the full report today.
            </h2>
            <div>
              <Button color="blue" text="Download" href="#form"/>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  

 
